l.description: Loads device LogicType to register by housing index value.

s.description: Stores register value to LogicType on device by housing index value.

ls.description: Loads slot LogicSlotType on device to register.

lr.description: Loads reagent of device's ReagentMode where a hash of the reagent type to check for. ReagentMode can be either Contents (0), Required (1), Recipe (2). Can use either the word, or the number.

sb.description: Stores register value to LogicType on all output network devices with provided type hash.

lb.description: Loads LogicType from all output network devices with provided type hash using the provide batch mode. Average (0), Sum (1), Minimum (2), Maximum (3). Can use either the word, or the number.

alias.description: Labels register or device reference with name, device references also affect what shows on the screws on the IC base.

move.description: Register = provided num or register value.

sdse.description: Register = 1 if device is set, otherwise 0.

sdns.description: Register = 1 if device is not set, otherwise 0

sap.description: Register = 1 if abs(a - b) <= max(c \* max(abs(a), abs(b)), float.epsilon \* 8), otherwise 0

sna.description: Register = 1 if abs(a - b) > max(c \* max(abs(a), abs(b)), float.epsilon \* 8), otherwise 0

and.description: Performs a bitwise logical AND operation on the binary representation of two values. Each bit of the result is determined by evaluating the corresponding bits of the input values. If both bits are 1, the resulting bit is set to 1. Otherwise the resulting bit is set to 0.

or.description: Performs a bitwise logical OR operation on the binary representation of two values. Each bit of the result is determined by evaluating the corresponding bits of the input values. If either bit is 1, the resulting bit is set to 1. If both bits are 0, the resulting bit is set to 0.

xor.description: Performs a bitwise logical XOR (exclusive OR) operation on the binary representation of two values. Each bit of the result is determined by evaluating the corresponding bits of the input values. If the bits are different (one bit is 0 and the other is 1), the resulting bit is set to 1. If the bits are the same (both 0 or both 1), the resulting bit is set to 0.

nor.description: Performs a bitwise logical NOR (NOT OR) operation on the binary representation of two values. Each bit of the result is determined by evaluating the corresponding bits of the input values. If both bits are 0, the resulting bit is set to 1. Otherwise, if at least one bit is 1, the resulting bit is set to 0.

mod.description: Register = a mod b (note: NOT a % b)

bgez.description: Branch to line b if a >= 0

blez.description: Branch to line b if a <= 0

bgtz.description: Branch to line b if a > 0

bdns.description: Branch to line a if device d isn't set

beq.description: Branch to line c if a == b

bne.description: Branch to line c if a != b

bap.description: Branch to line d if abs(a - b) <= max(c \* max(abs(a), abs(b)), float.epsilon \* 8)

bna.description: Branch to line d if abs(a - b) > max(c \* max(abs(a), abs(b)), float.epsilon \* 8)

brdns.description: Relative jump to line a if device is not set

bneal.description: Branch to line c if a != b and store next line number in ra

bdnsal.description: Jump execution to line a and store next line number if device is not set

brgez.description: Relative branch to line b if a >= 0

brlez.description: Relative branch to line b if a <= 0

brgtz.description: Relative branch to line b if a > 0

brne.description: Relative branch to line c if a != b

brna.description: Relative branch to line d if abs(a - b) > max(c \* max(abs(a), abs(b)), float.epsilon \* 8)

trunc.description: Register = a with fractional part removed

floor.description: Register = largest integer less than a

min.description: Register = min of a or b

abs.description: Register = the absolute value of a

peek.description: Register = the value at the top of the stack

push.description: Pushes the value of a to the stack at sp and increments sp

pop.description: Register = the value at the top of the stack and decrements sp

select.description: Register = b if a is non-zero, otherwise c

bgt.description: Branch to line c if a > b

ble.description: Branch to line c if a <= b

bge.description: Branch to line c if a >= b

brgt.description: relative jump to line c if a > b

brle.description: Relative jump to line c if a <= b

brge.description: Relative jump to line c if a >= b

bapz.description: Branch to line c if abs(a) <= float.epsilon \* 8

define.description: Creates a label that will be replaced throughout the program with the provided value.

sleep.description: Pauses execution on the IC for a seconds

sin.description: Returns the sine of the specified angle (radians)

asin.description: Returns the angle (radians) whos sine is the specified value

tan.description: Returns the tan of the specified angle (radians)

atan.description: Returns the angle (radians) whos tan is the specified value

cos.description: Returns the cosine of the specified angle (radians)

acos.description: Returns the cosine of the specified angle (radians)

atan2.description: Returns the angle (radians) whose tangent is the quotient of two specified values: a (y) and b (x)

brnan.description: Relative branch to line b if a is not a number (NaN)

bnan.description: Branch to line b if a is not a number (NaN)

snan.description: Register = 1 if a is NaN, otherwise 0

snanz.description: Register = 0 if a is NaN, otherwise 1

lbs.description: Loads LogicSlotType from slotIndex from all output network devices with provided type hash using the provide batch mode. Average (0), Sum (1), Minimum (2), Maximum (3). Can use either the word, or the number.

lbn.description: Loads LogicType from all output network devices with provided type and name hashes using the provide batch mode. Average (0), Sum (1), Minimum (2), Maximum (3). Can use either the word, or the number.

sbn.description: Stores register value to LogicType on all output network devices with provided type hash and name.

lbns.description: Loads LogicSlotType from slotIndex from all output network devices with provided type and name hashes using the provide batch mode. Average (0), Sum (1), Minimum (2), Maximum (3). Can use either the word, or the number.

ss.description: Stores register value to device stored in a slot LogicSlotType on device.

sbs.description: Stores register value to LogicSlotType on all output network devices with provided type hash in the provided slot.

srl.description: Performs a bitwise logical right shift operation on the binary representation of a value. It shifts the bits to the right and fills the vacated leftmost bits with zeros

sra.description: Performs a bitwise arithmetic right shift operation on the binary representation of a value. It shifts the bits to the right and fills the vacated leftmost bits with a copy of the sign bit (the most significant bit).

sll.description: Performs a bitwise logical left shift operation on the binary representation of a value. It shifts the bits to the left and fills the vacated rightmost bits with zeros.

sla.description: Performs a bitwise arithmetic left shift operation on the binary representation of a value. It shifts the bits to the left and fills the vacated rightmost bits with a copy of the sign bit (the most significant bit).

not.description: Performs a bitwise logical NOT operation flipping each bit of the input value, resulting in a binary complement. If a bit is 1, it becomes 0, and if a bit is 0, it becomes 1.

ld.description: Loads device LogicType to register by direct ID reference.

sd.description: Stores register value to LogicType on device by direct ID reference.

poke.description: Stores the provided value at the provided address in the stack.

getd.description: Seeks directly for the provided device id, attempts to read the stack value at the provided address, and places it in the register.

putd.description: Seeks directly for the provided device id, attempts to write the provided value to the stack at the provided address.

get.description: Using the provided device, attempts to read the stack value at the provided address, and places it in the register.

put.description: Using the provided device, attempts to write the provided value to the stack at the provided address.

clr.description: Clears the stack memory for the provided device.

clrd.description: Seeks directly for the provided device id and clears the stack memory of that device

Acceleration.description: Change in velocity. Rockets that are deccelerating when landing will show this as negative value.

Activate.description: 1 if device is activated (usually means running), otherwise 0

AirRelease.description: The current state of the air release system, for example AirRelease = 1 for a Hardsuit sets Air Release to On

AlignmentError.description: The angular discrepancy between the telescope's current orientation and the target. Indicates how 'off target' the telescope is. Returns NaN when no target.

Apex.description: The lowest altitude that the rocket will reach before it starts travelling upwards again.

AutoLand.description: Engages the automatic landing algorithm. The rocket will automatically throttle and turn on and off its engines to achieve a smooth landing.

AutoShutOff.description: Turns off all devices in the rocket upon reaching destination

BestContactFilter.description: Filters the satellite's auto selection of targets to a single reference ID.

BurnTimeRemaining.description: Estimated time in seconds until fuel is depleted. Calculated based on current fuel usage.

CelestialHash.description: The current hash of the targeted celestial object.

CelestialParentHash.description: The hash for the name of the parent the celestial is orbiting, 0 if there is no parent celestial.

Channel0.description: Channel on a cable network which should be considered volatile

Channel1.description: Channel on a cable network which should be considered volatile

Channel2.description: Channel on a cable network which should be considered volatile

Channel3.description: Channel on a cable network which should be considered volatile

Channel4.description: Channel on a cable network which should be considered volatile

Channel5.description: Channel on a cable network which should be considered volatile

Channel6.description: Channel on a cable network which should be considered volatile

Channel7.description: Channel on a cable network which should be considered volatile

Charge.description: The current charge the device has

Chart.description: Progress status of Chart scan at the rocket's target Space Map Location. Returns a clamped normalised value. If Chart scan is not available returns -1.

ChartedNavPoints.description: The number of charted NavPoints at the rocket's target Space Map Location.

ClearMemory.description: When set to 1, clears the counter memory (e.g. ExportCount). Will set itself back to 0 when actioned

CollectableGoods.description: Gets the cost of fuel to return the rocket to your current world.

Color.description: Whether driven by concerns for clarity, safety or simple aesthetics, Stationeers have access to a small rainbow of colors for their constructions. These are the color setting for devices, represented as an integer. 0: Blue 1: Grey 2: Green 3: Orange 4: Red 5: Yellow 6: White 7: Black 8: Brown 9: Khaki 10: Pink 11: Purple It is an unwavering universal law that anything higher than 11 will be purple. The ODA is powerless to change this. Similarly, anything lower than 0 will be Blue.

Combustion.description: The assess atmosphere is on fire. Returns 1 if atmosphere is on fire, 0 if not.

CombustionInput.description: The assess atmosphere is on fire. Returns 1 if device's input network is on fire, 0 if not.

CombustionInput2.description: The assess atmosphere is on fire. Returns 1 if device's Input2 network is on fire, 0 if not.

CombustionLimiter.description: Retards the rate of combustion inside the machine (range: 0-100), with 0 being the slowest rate of combustion and 100 being the fastest

CombustionOutput.description: The assess atmosphere is on fire. Returns 1 if device's Output network is on fire, 0 if not.

CombustionOutput2.description: The assess atmosphere is on fire. Returns 1 if device's Output2 network is on fire, 0 if not.

CompletionRatio.description: How complete the current production is for this device, between 0 and 1

ContactTypeId.description: The type id of the contact.

CurrentCode.description: The Space Map Address of the rockets current Space Map Location

Density.description: The density of the rocket's target site's mine-able deposit.

DestinationCode.description: The Space Map Address of the rockets target Space Map Location

Discover.description: Progress status of Discovery scan at the rocket's target Space Map Location. Returns a clamped normalised value. If Discovery scan is not available returns -1.

DistanceAu.description: The current distance to the celestial object, measured in astronomical units.

DistanceKm.description: The current distance to the celestial object, measured in kilometers.

DrillCondition.description: The current condition of the drill head in this devices drill slot. Expressed as a ratio between 0 and 1.

DryMass.description: The Mass in kilograms of the rocket excluding fuel. The more massive the rocket the more fuel will be required to move to a new location in space.

Eccentricity.description: A measure of how elliptical (oval) an orbit is. Ranges from 0 (a perfect circle) to 1 (a parabolic trajectory).

ElevatorLevel.description: Level the elevator is currently at

EntityState.description: The current entity state, such as whether it is dead, unconscious or alive, expressed as a state integer.

EnvironmentEfficiency.description: The Environment Efficiency reported by the machine, as a float between 0 and 1

Error.description: 1 if device is in error state, otherwise 0

ExhaustVelocity.description: The velocity of the exhaust gas in m/s

ExportCount.description: How many items exported since last ClearMemory

Filtration.description: The current state of the filtration system, for example Filtration = 1 for a Hardsuit sets filtration to On

FlightControlRule.description: Flight control rule of rocket. None = 0, No AutoPilot. Normal = 1, Target Decent Apex of 60m. Alternate = 2, Velocity to High - Full throttle. Alternate2 = 3, Target an appropriate decent velocity as velocity is too low. FinalApproach = 4, Descend towards launch mount in a controlled manner.

Flush.description: Set to 1 to activate the flush function on the device

ForceWrite.description: Forces Logic Writer devices to rewrite value

ForwardX.description: The direction the entity is facing expressed as a normalized vector

ForwardY.description: The direction the entity is facing expressed as a normalized vector

ForwardZ.description: The direction the entity is facing expressed as a normalized vector

Fuel.description: Gets the cost of fuel to return the rocket to your current world.

Harvest.description: Performs the harvesting action for any plant based machinery

HorizontalRatio.description: Radio of horizontal setting for device

Idle.description: Returns 1 if the device is currently idle, otherwise 0

ImportCount.description: How many items imported since last ClearMemory

Inclination.description: The tilt of an orbit's plane relative to the equatorial plane, measured in degrees. Defines the orbital plane's angle.

Index.description: The current index for the device.

InterrogationProgress.description: Progress of this sattellite dish's interrogation of its current target, as a ratio from 0-1

LineNumber.description: The line number of current execution for an integrated circuit running on this device. While this number can be written, use with caution

Lock.description: 1 if device is locked, otherwise 0, can be set in most devices and prevents the user from access the values

ManualResearchRequiredPod.description: Sets the pod type to search for a certain pod when breaking down a pods.

Mass.description: The total Mass of the rocket in kilograms including fuel and cargo. The more massive the rocket the more fuel will be required to move to a new location in space.

MineablesInQueue.description: Returns the amount of mineables AIMEe has queued up to mine.

MineablesInVicinity.description: Returns the amount of potential mineables within an extended area around AIMEe.

MinedQuantity.description: The total number of resources that have been mined at the rocket's target Space Map Site.

MinimumWattsToContact.description: Minimum required amount of watts from the dish hitting the target trader contact to start interrogating the contact

Mode.description: Integer for mode state, different devices will have different mode states available to them

NameHash.description: Provides the hash value for the name of the object as a 32 bit integer.

NavPoints.description: The number of NavPoints at the rocket's target Space Map Location.

NextWeatherEventTime.description: Returns in seconds when the next weather event is inbound.

On.description: The current state of the device, 0 for off, 1 for on

OperationalTemperatureEfficiency.description: How the input pipe's temperature effects the machines efficiency

OrbitPeriod.description: The time it takes for an object to complete one full orbit around another object, measured in days. Indicates the duration of the orbital cycle.

Orientation.description: The orientation of the entity in degrees in a plane relative towards the north origin

Output.description: The output operation for a sort handling device, such as a stacker or sorter, when in logic mode the device will only action one repetition when set zero or above and then back to -1 and await further instructions

PassedMoles.description: The number of moles that passed through this device on the previous simulation tick

ReEntryAltitude.description: The altitude that the rocket will begin its decent to the pad. Must be between 25km and 120km

Reagents.description: Total number of reagents recorded by the device

RecipeHash.description: Current hash of the recipe the device is set to produce

ReferenceId.description: Unique Reference Identifier for this object

RequestHash.description: When set to the unique identifier, requests an item of the provided type from the device

RequiredPower.description: Idle operating power quantity, does not necessarily include extra demand power

ReturnFuelCost.description: Gets the fuel remaining in your rocket's fuel tank.

Richness.description: The richness of the rocket's target site's mine-able deposit.

Rpm.description: The number of revolutions per minute that the device's spinning mechanism is doing

SemiMajorAxis.description: The longest radius of an elliptical orbit in astronomical units, measuring half the major axis. Determines the size of the orbit.

Setting.description: A variable setting that can be read or written, depending on the device

SignalID.description: Returns the contact ID of the strongest signal from this Satellite

SignalStrength.description: Returns the degree offset of the strongest contact

Sites.description: The number of Sites that have been discovered at the rockets target Space Map location.

Size.description: The size of the rocket's target site's mine-able deposit.

SizeX.description: Size on the X (right) axis of the object in largeGrids (a largeGrid is 2meters)

SizeY.description: Size on the Y(Up) axis of the object in largeGrids (a largeGrid is 2meters)

SizeZ.description: Size on the Z(Forward) axis of the object in largeGrids (a largeGrid is 2meters)

SoundAlert.description: Plays a sound alert on the devices speaker

Stress.description: Machines get stressed when working hard. When Stress reaches 100 the machine will automatically shut down

Survey.description: Progress status of Survey scan at the rocket's target Space Map Location. Returns a normalised value where 100% surveyed is equal to 1. If Survey scan is not available returns -1.

TargetPadIndex.description: The index of the trader landing pad on this devices data network that it will try to call a trader in to land

TargetX.description: The target position in X dimension in world coordinates

TargetY.description: The target position in Y dimension in world coordinates

TargetZ.description: The target position in Z dimension in world coordinates

Temperature.description: The current temperature reading of the device

TemperatureDifferentialEfficiency.description: How the difference between the input pipe and waste pipe temperatures effect the machines efficiency

TemperatureExternal.description: The temperature of the outside of the device, usually the world atmosphere surrounding it

TemperatureInput.description: The current temperature reading of the device's Input Network

TemperatureInput2.description: The current temperature reading of the device's Input2 Network

TemperatureOutput.description: The current temperature reading of the device's Output Network

TemperatureOutput2.description: The current temperature reading of the device's Output2 Network

TemperatureSetting.description: The current setting for the internal temperature of the object (e.g. the Hardsuit A/C)

Throttle.description: Increases the rate at which the machine works (range: 0-100)

Thrust.description: Total current thrust of all rocket engines on the rocket in Newtons.

ThrustToWeight.description: Ratio of thrust to weight of rocket. Weight is effected by local body gravity. A rocket with a low thrust to weight will expend more fuel during launch and landing.

TimeToDestination.description: Estimated time in seconds until rocket arrives at target destination.

TotalMolesInput2.description: Returns the total moles of the device's Input2 Network

TotalMolesOutput.description: Returns the total moles of the device's Output Network

TotalMolesOutput2.description: Returns the total moles of the device's Output2 Network

TotalQuantity.description: The estimated total quantity of resources available to mine at the rocket's target Space Map Site.

TrueAnomaly.description: An angular parameter that defines the position of a body moving along a Keplerian orbit. It is the angle between the direction of periapsis and the current position of the body, as seen from the main focus of the ellipse (the point around which the object orbits).

VelocityMagnitude.description: The current magnitude of the velocity vector

VelocityRelativeX.description: The current velocity X relative to the forward vector of this

VelocityRelativeY.description: The current velocity Y relative to the forward vector of this

VelocityRelativeZ.description: The current velocity Z relative to the forward vector of this

VelocityX.description: The world velocity of the entity in the X axis

VelocityY.description: The world velocity of the entity in the Y axis

VelocityZ.description: The world velocity of the entity in the Z axis

VerticalRatio.description: Radio of vertical setting for device

VolumeOfLiquid.description: The total volume of all liquids in Liters in the atmosphere

WattsReachingContact.description: The amount of watts actually hitting the contact. This is effected by the power of the dish and how far off-axis the dish is from the contact vector

Weight.description: Weight of Rocket in Newtons (Including fuel and cargo). Weight is effected by local body gravity.

WorkingGasEfficiency.description: The Working Gas Efficiency reported by the machine, as a float between 0 and 1
